subSubSection.paragraph:
Abdomen. With a lateral tuft of setulae on syntergite 1+2; tergites 3–5 with setae laterally; tergite 4 with setae apically and tergite 5 with a few discal setae; sternite 1 setulose; posterior margin of sternite 5 concave and with setae on membrane (
Fig. 144
).

Terminalia. Outer margin of cercal plate slightly convex; cercal plate ventrally with one strong spine (
Figs 145–147
); surstylus with 3 setae basally; aedeagus with spicules on anterior membrane of distiphallus; gonopod with 2 setae on basal half; paramere with a few setulae on apical half (
Fig. 148
).

Ovipositor. Tergite 6 as 2 rods; tergite 7 as 2 rods, posteriorly with 2 small round plates with 3–5 very small spines; tergite 8 as 2 rods, posteriorly enlarged; sternite 6 as 1 rod, posteriorly with a few very small setae; sternite 7 as 1 rod, posteriorly with 3 round plates with spines; sternite 8 as 2 very small plates with very small setulae; enlarged spicules on intersegmental membrane between segments 6–7 and 7–8; epiproct longer than wide with about 2 setae and 2 setulae; hypoproct with many setae; cercus flattened and not long (
Figs 149–150
).
